ate some fresh light on several familiar issues. First, I pursue a reading of Marx focused on his treatment of subjectivity, individuation, and related methodological and practical matters; second, I apply this interpretation to analyzing the dispute between Marxist orthodoxy and heterodoxy over such matters as class consciousness and the philosophy of materialism; finally, I employ this historical context to clarify the significance of ";existential Marxism,"; Maurice Merleau-Ponty's and Jean-Paul Sartre's contribution to Marxist thought.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 7aPHILOSOPHY / Political.2bisacsh  aclass consciousness.  acommunism.  aexistential philosophy.  ahistorians.  ahistorical context.  ahistorical perspective.  ahuman existence.  aindividual emancipation.  aindividuality.  aindividuation.  ajean paul sartre.  amarx.  amarxism.  amarxist orthodoxy.  amarxist theory.  amerleau ponty.  amethodological.  anonfiction essay.  aphilosophical.  aphilosophy of materialism.  apolitical philosophy.  apolitical science.  asocial theory.  asocialist thought.  asubjective thought.  asystematic thought.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Package Archive Pre-2000z97831106353480 cprintz978052004779240uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052034086240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520340862423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520340862/original  a978-3-11-063534-8  University of California Press Package Archive Pre-2000b2000  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-UCY